ntifying that is important for you to plan the remaining logistics.","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"cEpvTg5Q69"}],"key":"TVvvtSotH9"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A few other scenarios could be:","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1},"end":{"line":24,"column":1}},"key":"KTv0dZ1bWS"}],"key":"lLw7bBJqVA"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you work from home, you would like to see your colleagues and stay connected with them through designated coworking schedules.","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":25,"column":1}},"key":"UTySRkjYVU"}],"key":"MxdyA9WCCL"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you are working with a distributed group of people on a common project, and if communication and exchange related to the project while working asynchronously is an issue, you can get a lot of your work done over a coworking call.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"sHreN2341R"}],"key":"hrdAE4Tc70"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1},"end":{"line":27,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you are working on multiple projects and struggle to focus on one task at a time, coworking can help you put aside a few hours of your time to work with your colleagues who you share the project with.","position":{"start":{"line":27,"column":1},"end":{"line":27,"column":1}},"key":"CB9On8G2wO"}],"key":"rlmZwI5hD4"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If there is a task you are struggling to complete, you can invite support from your trusted colleagues through coworking calls.","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":1},"end":{"line":28,"column":1}},"key":"rLwSTjRyU0"}],"key":"ul1QOGf7aj"}],"key":"Iz8N8Jl6MR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Target audience","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":30,"column":1}},"key":"sHLClydedc"}],"key":"fdLwhfUBGD"}],"key":"DqxjcaQhpA"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you already know the purpose of your coworking calls, you will be able to identify who your target audience is.","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1},"end":{"line":32,"column":1}},"key":"nmImO1YBiP"}],"key":"feboLLwqdM"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":35,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For example, if you host your coworking calls for an open source project such as ","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"jh4nMmdBfm"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"IdXygXBLL9"}],"key":"ZAXUx1RvbL"},{"type":"text","value":", you can expect your current members, past contributors or even new members of the project to participate.\nIf you are part of a small project, you would expect the same familiar faces in all your coworking calls.","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":1},"end":{"line":34,"column":1}},"key":"ou4T2iKa0A"}],"key":"LS3MppRiIj"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Organisers and hosts","position":{"start":{"line":37,"column":1},"end":{"line":37,"column":1}},"key":"UdwLaznm9f"}],"key":"qCnnJNl2EU"}],"key":"n5fCj9utaW"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Many tasks go into organising a coworking call.\nThese tasks can be taken care of by one person like a community manager, project manager, or a volunteer organiser.\nHowever, it is always a good idea to involve more people as co-organisers so that the coworking call still happens even when the main organiser can’t join for any reason.\nTo avoid one person burdening themselves with “not so exciting” organisation issues, you can also decide to rotate the role within the members of your project.","position":{"start":{"line":39,"column":1},"end":{"line":39,"column":1}},"key":"QOk4nDb7By"}],"key":"AcKy7ximiD"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Size of the call","position":{"start":{"line":44,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"key":"FDFBg19BT2"}],"key":"yeZNMCMW7B"}],"key":"cRxN2NFuBu"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":49,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"No matter what the purpose and who the target audience of your calls are, you can decide the size of your call by managing participation by prior registration.\nIf you organise these calls for your project members on a mutually agreed time and with an agenda to work on specific tasks, you can expect most of them to show up.\nIf you keep your call open for any of your community members to join, you may end up having a different number of participants on different calls.\nThis would also mean that for some calls, there won’t be anyone available to co-work with you.","position":{"start":{"line":46,"column":1},"end":{"line":46,"column":1}},"key":"OsJv4wE0C8"}],"key":"TvrowOvpfz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":52,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It’s useful to handle some sort of sign-up sheet or registration system so the organisers know who to expect on the call.\nIn ","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"Woq30qeCh5"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"moRm0geKSJ"}],"key":"QRW3lpqHrn"},{"type":"text","value":", we use dedicated HackMD notes that can be updated before each call by the participants.","position":{"start":{"line":51,"column":1},"end":{"line":51,"column":1}},"key":"d8JBuclmDa"}],"key":"nP2d5fnjmC"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Frequency of these calls","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1},"end":{"line":54,"column":1}},"key":"lVhtHH0Fsp"}],"key":"YL9FGPZMkp"}],"key":"BY4jg20X0H"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":57,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once you have identified the purpose, target audience and size of your calls, you can decide how often you would like to host them.\nIf you work with the same group of people, you can host it as per your common availability and at a mutually agreed time on a weekly or monthly basis.","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1},"end":{"line":56,"column":1}},"key":"mlm382d88J"}],"key":"ayd9WiDomX"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":61,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If the expected participants of your call also work on multiple projects, you might consider regularly hosting it on the same day and time each week or each month.\nThis consistency will allow them to check their availability in advance and block these hours in their calendar.\nThis will also reduce the extra work of coordinating the common availability every time (though you will have to do this in the beginning).","position":{"start":{"line":59,"column":1},"end":{"line":59,"column":1}},"key":"rIxjPwbJ2e"}],"key":"OBAdPfbSGA"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Resource availability","position":{"start":{"line":63,"column":1},"end":{"line":63,"column":1}},"key":"SjjcNldxUf"}],"key":"CNjheXrVa7"}],"key":"NOBYC38DJT"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Based on the resources available to you, you might have to fine-tune other aspects of your call.","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":1},"end":{"line":65,"column":1}},"key":"MNXxJAucaz"}],"key":"cPOqCHNDhT"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For example:","position":{"start":{"line":67,"column":1},"end":{"line":67,"column":1}},"key":"nZUQ6P2W4C"}],"key":"y9faB9OEgJ"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":72,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":68,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":68,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Shared calendar","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":68,"column":1}},"key":"zuU3cupESF"}],"key":"vPfC4gh1BD"},{"type":"text","value":": If there is a calendar that is updated with a schedule of the coworking calls, people can subscribe to it and indicate their availability.","position":{"start":{"line":68,"column":1},"end":{"line":68,"column":1}},"key":"ZMWqgMQIc2"}],"key":"pyZaqFk3tl"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Communication platforms","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"DTUrf5CIAi"}],"key":"U1l0QYiNr8"},{"type":"text","value":": software like Zoom can allow you to connect with many people at the same time. However, you will need a paid subscription (pro account) to control who joins your call (by activating waiting room to avoid Zoom bombing), manage breakout rooms (to allow multiple small groups and discussions) or host longer calls (>40 minutes).","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":1},"end":{"line":69,"column":1}},"key":"DQCIOP8eVR"}],"key":"PbEncevZIO"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":72,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Chat system","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"key":"dann1J1gPN"}],"key":"cAxFt8bwuG"},{"type":"text","value":": If you have a group Slack or Gitter channel, information can be exchanged with everyone, including those who can not join the calls but want to offer suggestions or carry out related tasks asynchronously but in coordination with the group.\nThis also allows people to keep each other informed of any last-minute changes such as updated links for joining calls, correct notes, or cancellation of calls.","position":{"start":{"line":70,"column":1},"end":{"line":70,"column":1}},"key":"DpRp4PPfox"}],"key":"oQZsZ6DbS0"}],"key":"wUB6xMzS9s"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Logistics and tasks","position":{"start":{"line":73,"column":1},"end":{"line":73,"column":1}},"key":"YcOlIL2kA4"}],"identifier":"logistics-and-tasks","label":"Logistics and tasks","html_id":"logistics-and-tasks","implicit":true,"key":"BKYPg1swoS"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Like any event, coworking calls require planning, organising, hosting and making sure that they happen.","position":{"start":{"line":75,"column":1},"end":{"line":75,"column":1}},"key":"tMot2bcAHj"}],"key":"xkU1mDtxcr"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As the organiser/s of the event, you will be required to:","position":{"start":{"line":77,"column":1},"end":{"line":77,"column":1}},"key":"RoEmoqe0S2"}],"key":"xC9iHGImXG"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1. Choose the tools","position":{"start":{"line":79,"column":1},"end":{"line":79,"column":1}},"key":"lQDX0MERCF"}],"key":"dGn4clcT2M"}],"key":"htzjnMoyxa"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":81,"column":1},"end":{"line":82,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The choice in regards to which tools you will use will depend on the purpose and scope of your calls.\nPlease see the subchapter ","position":{"