gned their call format for the Jean Golding Institute’s community members in Bristol to work together and build connections while working on their data science projects.\nThis is a great example of using coworking calls for community building and supporting others with similar research interests.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"M81pMyJe75"}],"key":"JI48fw0gMG"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Small groups for supporting each other","position":{"start":{"line":119,"column":1},"end":{"line":119,"column":1}},"key":"xoWazlbEAG"}],"identifier":"small-groups-for-supporting-each-other","label":"Small groups for supporting each other","html_id":"small-groups-for-supporting-each-other","implicit":true,"key":"OBI4dhdHDy"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":122,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can also plan your coworking calls with a small group of (2-3) colleagues with whom you can mutually hold accountability for your time and work.\nA small group reduces the burden of coordinating multiple time zones and finding a schedule that is suitable for everyone.","position":{"start":{"line":121,"column":1},"end":{"line":121,"column":1}},"key":"PMvLiBRVaY"}],"key":"kZcmMv8FOR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":125,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Naomi Penfold and Stefanie Butland have written about their 1:1 coworking format in this post: ","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"key":"QY1h0KjLKS"},{"type":"link","url":"https://www.cscce.org/2020/02/04/online-co-working-partnerships-are-community-of-practice-in-action/#more-3009","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Online Co-working Partnerships are Community of Practice in Action","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"key":"S54CzMzbJ7"}],"urlSource":"https://www.cscce.org/2020/02/04/online-co-working-partnerships-are-community-of-practice-in-action/#more-3009","key":"CBK2NUU2Xk"},{"type":"text","value":".\nWhile reviewing this chapter, Naomi described their 1:1 call format in contrast with ","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"key":"fS2xbY0JG4"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Turing Way","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"key":"UeOQGFrgKD"}],"key":"ElCkwauiZJ"},{"type":"text","value":" group format as follows:","position":{"start":{"line":124,"column":1},"end":{"line":124,"column":1}},"key":"NsHacUjlk2"}],"key":"Aui58AmpIS"},{"type":"blockquote","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":130,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In the co-working calls I have, it’s 1:1 and we often spend 20 minutes, in the beginning, catching up and talking about our progress since last time.\nIf there is something we want to discuss more intensely, we allocate 30 minutes of our call time to that, for example, one of us asking the other how to troubleshoot something.\nFor the time in between, we do a few quiet working sessions (sometimes 25 minutes, sometimes longer).\nThis is likely a combination of a co-mentoring call and a co-working Pomodoro call, and it works well for me.","position":{"start":{"line":127,"column":1},"end":{"line":127,"column":1}},"key":"heRp6jbNav"}],"key":"A73EPdytzv"}],"key":"paJVFL3FsR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":132,"column":1},"end":{"line":132,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"You can read an adapted version of